                            <p style="font-family:'Conv_MYRIADPRO-BOLD_1',sans-serif;"> <span>What is <span style="font-weight: bolder;">diabesity?</span></span> This is the condition of being obese and also having Type 2 Diabetes as a result of excess weight.</p>

                            <p>Morbid obesity increases your risk of developing Type 2 Diabetes and that risk can be reduced with weight loss. There has been a rapid increase in the prevalence of Type 2 Diabetes, Obesity and associated complications such as an increased risk of heart attack, stroke, certain cancers, blindness, kidney failure etc.</p>

                            <p><span>What <span style="font-weight: bolder;font-family: 'Conv_MYRIADPRO-BOLD_1',sans-serif;">simply</span>weight’s <span style="font-weight: bolder;font-family: 'Conv_MYRIADPRO-BOLD_1',sans-serif;">‘‘diabesity’’</span> programme does:</span> </p>
                            <p>The <span style="font-family: 'Conv_MYRIADPRO-BOLD_1',sans-serif;color: rgb(38, 38, 38);">diabesity</span> programme helps you to prevent Type 2 Diabetes by managing your weight. If you have prediabetes or are at risk of developing Type 2 Diabetes, this programme is suitable for you. <span>The 100-Day <span style="font-weight: bolder;">diabesity</span> programme</span> helps you lose weight while placing a strong emphasis on preventing Type 2 Diabetes. Our Diabetes Specialists will provide you with medical guidance throughout the programme.</p>
                            <p>For full details, please <a href="https://www.simplyweight.co.uk/diabesity_detail/" target="_blank">click here</a></p>
